# Design System Reference

The complete MDZN Partners UI Design System is located at `references/design-system.md`. This is the single source of truth for all visual decisions.

## Before Any UI or Design Work

You MUST read `references/design-system.md` in full before creating or modifying any UI element. Do NOT assume you know the system. Read it every time.

## What the Design System Covers

- **Color System** — Arctic Navy palette with gold accent. Primary scale (Slate), Secondary (Navy), Accent (Gold), Semantic colors, Surfaces.
- **Typography** — Plus Jakarta Sans. Type scale from Display 1 (72px) to Overline (11px). Negative letter-spacing on headlines.
- **Spacing & Grid** — 8px base unit. 12-column grid. Section spacing. Breakpoints.
- **Components** — Buttons (Primary, Secondary, Accent, Ghost), Navigation, Border Radius, Shadows.
- **Glass Effects** — Soft Glass style. Only on gradient/textured backgrounds.
- **Icons** — Lucide icons in geometric containers echoing the MDZN logo.
- **Illustrations** — Floating Window style, flat (0°) perspective, deep shadow.
- **Motion** — Subtle animations. Fast (150ms), Base (200ms), Slow (300ms). Only transform + opacity.
- **Interaction States** — Warm & Engaging. Gold accent on hover. Scale(0.98) on active. Gold glow ring on buttons.
- **Do's & Don'ts** — Strict guidelines on what to follow and what to avoid.

## Non-Negotiable Rules

- Every color must come from the design system palette. No custom colors.
- Every spacing value must be a multiple of 8px.
- Every border radius must use the defined tokens (6/8/12/16/20px).
- Typography must use Plus Jakarta Sans with the defined weights and sizes.
- Interaction states must follow the Warm & Engaging pattern (gold accent on hover).
- Glass effects are only used on gradient or textured backgrounds.
- Gold accent is used sparingly -- emphasis only, never for large backgrounds or body text.
- No pure black (#000) -- always use primary-900 (#0F172A).
- No decorative elements without purpose.

## Who Must Follow This

All agents involved in UI work: **Designer**, **Head of Design**, **Developer**, **Head of Engineering**, **Tester** (for design fidelity checks). When in doubt, check the design system.
